!ys-0

# YS values are JVM objects. A static method is called with the
# Class/method form; an instance method uses the (. object method args)
# Java interop form.

defn main(text='Hello, World!'):
  # Static (class) method:
  say: Long/toBinaryString(42)

  # Instance methods on a String object:
  say: (. text toUpperCase)
  say: (. text indexOf 'World')
